{"word":"ἄμητος","slug":"ἄμητος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄμητος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἀμάω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a reaping, harvesting</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b> (<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of <i>slaughter</i>).<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>harvest, harvest time</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>the crop</i> or <i>harvest reaped</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>seges</el>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}